# MIDAS documentation scope (`doc.mdc`)

Applies when editing `docs/`, `deploy/ecs-app/docker/`, `deploy/ecs-app/helm/`, `deploy/scripts/`, `.cursor/scripts/`, or `deploy/Jenkinsfile_Deploy_App` (when that Jenkinsfile affects Docker build, ECR push, or Helm deploy).

## Rules

- Match the existing layout and conventions in the tree you touch. Do not expand scope into unrelated paths.
- For scripts, self-documenting code is enough (`--help`, header comments). Do not create `README.md` files unless the user asks.
- For Terraform and AWS infrastructure, follow `.cursor/rules/solution_const.mdc` (identifiers) and `.cursor/rules/architecture.mdc` (design principles).
